BEFORE--------------------
1- my website was running on AWS using ec2 instances, we have deployed services using docker-compose on container on ec2 whcih is routing using nginx ingress, ssl managed by cert manager lets encrypt, some services routing by rote53 using public ip, orchestration done by docker swarm
2- bitbucket for code repo
3- jenkins for ci-cd
4- orchestration by docker swarm
5- ssl by lets encypt auto renewl by cert-manager
6- db using RDS MySQL
7- auto scale by ASG

all are running in docker container on different ec2

AFTER--------------------
1- setup eks cluster(dev, stage, prod) 
   argocd, AWS load Balancer, Grafana, prometheus
2- fetch cleaned yaml from docker-compose to deplyment.yaml, service.yaml
3- yaml pushed on bitbucket with different branch, dev, stage, prod
4- routing behined ALB 
5- WAF rule implemented for security
6- db and VPC are same as before with some networking SG changes
7- CDN implemented
8- SES implemented
9- generic webhook setup on bitbucket so that if code pushed on development branch jenkins pipeline run automatically
